# PCA-Based Home Loan Customer Analysis

## Project Overview
This project applies **Principal Component Analysis (PCA)** on a short-term home loan dataset to reduce dimensionality, identify important customer-loan behavior patterns, and flag customers who may show advance-closure or delayed-closure tendencies.

The analysis uses multiple loan-related numerical variables such as disbursement value, asset cost, receivable amount, overdue amount, tenure, installment amount, balance amount, payment behavior, and closure-related variables.

## Objective
The main objective of this project is to use PCA to simplify a high-dimensional home loan dataset and generate meaningful customer-level insights for loan monitoring and risk analysis.

## Business Problem
Financial institutions handle large amounts of loan data with many interrelated variables. Analyzing all variables individually can be difficult and time-consuming. PCA helps reduce the number of variables while retaining most of the important information from the dataset.

This project helps identify:

- Major hidden patterns in loan repayment behavior
- Customers with possible advance-closure tendency
- Customers with possible delayed-closure tendency
- Important dimensions affecting loan performance
